<br>
I don't get hung up on it, as it's a message board, but I know I wouldn't put up with it from my friends, or for an eq example, in my guild chat.<br>
<br>
Using the word &quot;fag&quot; as a putdown, implies that there is something wrong with being a fag.  People don't use the word &quot;straight&quot; as a putdown - it's intention, not audience.  Some gay people do use &quot;breeder&quot; as a putdown - I'm not a big fan, but again, I understand where and when it's appropriate - which I think is where PCness has a point.  Using racist, sexist, homophobic slurs in public indicates acceptance of the degradation of that race, gender, sexual orientation.<br>
<br>
Using it among friends may be fine when there is the comfort level to recognize that you're quite willing to accept people's differences - it's the public part that puts it out there that hey, it's cool to disparage people on these bases.<br>
<br>
And try as I might, I can't help but dislike people that toss around &quot;fag&quot; on the board all the time.  No rez for you.<br>
