<br>
Andross, allow me to shatter your preconceptions.  As a student of religion, (with a good background in the Hebrew Old Testament), allow me to enlighten you.<br>
<br>
1) <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> i dont know what God you are talking about but the God of the Bible DOES say that homosexuality is wrong (see Exodus 18:22, Exodus 20:13, etc<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Exodus was written by what scholars have deemed &quot;The Priestly Tradition&quot; author.  In other words, it is a collaboration of ancient Hebrew Rabbinic leaders who put those laws together.  They weren't in the 10 commandments, and from the character of God we can discern from other chapters, it doesn't look like God said that.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The reason Homosexuals have been called &quot;gay&quot; &quot;fag&quot; &quot;queer&quot; is that our nation WAS founded on Christian ideas and we USED to know Scripture better, since the majority of the people living in America in its early stages were Christian<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
       a)  Hate to break it to you, but this nation wasn't founded on Christian principles.  The founding fathers may have nominally been &quot;Christian,&quot; but they were actually Deists, as was the the intellectual trend of the day. In other words, they believed in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> a</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> God, not <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> the</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> God, and they dismissed the Resurrection and other miracles as superstition.  They also did their best to include the Establishment Clause and the Separation Clause in the constitution to ensure there would be no state-sponsored religion and have England 2.0.<br>
<br>
       b)  We didn't used to &quot;know&quot; better.  The social climate was a lot more hateful and intolerant, despite what the Leave it to Beaver reruns tell you.  <br>
<br>
       c)  Basically you are saying, at one point, everyone was more moral and KNEW that being gay was wrong, so we started calling people we didn't like faggots and gays to show them the error of their ways.  Tell me how much sense that makes.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
3)  <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Why do people have gay-pride parades?<br>
Why do people have to protest for equal rights to gays?<br>
Why do people have to fight to have gay marriages approved?<br>
Why arent there heterosexual parades?<br>
Why don't heterosexual's protest to have equal rights?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
        a)  They protest because for centuries, they've been treated as second-class citizens, beaten, discriminated against, killed, lynched, tortured, and generally made to feel lower that dog-shit.  Can you blame them for wanting to be treated like a human being?<br>
<br>
        b)   There are no heterosexual parades because it's the norm.  You completely take for granted that your life is completely accepted by everyone else and tolerated.  Pretend you are a Jew in an all-WASP community, and then you might begin to see what I mean.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
